1
00:00:00,818 --> 00:00:03,537
Hurry up and leave...

2
00:00:04,799 --> 00:00:06,316
Looks like you've gotten yourself wet...

3
00:00:06,803 --> 00:00:08,368
Thank you.

4
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:12,106
You're very pretty.

5
00:00:13,297 --> 00:00:15,645
What madness has caused you to like this girl?

6
00:00:15,645 --> 00:00:17,747
This girl has gotten The Red Paper before.

7
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,435
Wait a minute!

8
00:00:27,574 --> 00:00:29,109
They've kissed!

9
00:00:34,432 --> 00:00:36,044
Don't say it so loudly.

10
00:00:36,044 --> 00:00:38,534
Good for you, Tsukushi!

11
00:00:38,534 --> 00:00:40,418
It's not good at all,
in fact it's horrible.

12
00:00:40,418 --> 00:00:42,560
Don't you like him a lot?

13
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:43,959
How can I like her?

14
00:00:43,959 --> 00:00:46,600
You didn't kiss Hanazawa Rui?

15
00:00:47,519 --> 00:00:48,665
It was so horrible.

16
00:00:48,665 --> 00:00:49,715
But then,

17
00:00:49,715 --> 00:00:53,110
why would someone who considers you
his enemy, kiss you?

18
00:00:53,110 --> 00:00:55,619
That's why I think you two make the perfect pair.

19
00:00:55,619 --> 00:00:57,385
You've got to be kidding!
No way that's going to happen.

20
00:00:57,385 --> 00:01:01,867
Then, how is it that you two kissed
when both of you fell together?

21
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:05,665
Are you saying that I originally intended
to kiss that slut?

22
00:01:05,665 --> 00:01:09,252
The probability of that is high.

23
00:01:09,252 --> 00:01:10,523
Hey...

24
00:01:10,523 --> 00:01:12,355
How is that so?

25
00:01:13,090 --> 00:01:17,021
Your first kiss is was taken by your most hated person on earth.

26
00:01:17,021 --> 00:01:21,922
The two of you are fated to be together.

27
00:01:21,946 --> 00:01:22,747
That can't be true...

28
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:27,074
Your first kiss was taken by the man
you hated the most,

29
00:01:27,117 --> 00:01:28,240
Hang on, old lady.

30
00:01:28,271 --> 00:01:33,724
and it was right in front of the person
whom you liked the most.

31
00:01:37,183 --> 00:01:40,097
Why are you so interested in this?

32
00:01:40,097 --> 00:01:40,952
So...

33
00:01:40,952 --> 00:01:42,694
What was the feeling of your first kiss like?

34
00:01:43,515 --> 00:01:45,057
It is not the first kiss.

35
00:01:45,057 --> 00:01:47,316
But if I haven't gotten it wrong,
it indeed was your first kiss.

36
00:01:47,316 --> 00:01:48,598
No it isn't!

37
00:01:48,598 --> 00:01:50,991
As usual,
what Tsukasa does is different from other people.

38
00:01:50,991 --> 00:01:53,821
You people don't completely understand me

39
00:01:53,821 --> 00:01:55,152
When was it?

40
00:01:55,152 --> 00:01:55,882
Eh?

41
00:01:55,882 --> 00:01:58,926
If yesterday wasn't your first kiss,
then when was it?

42
00:01:58,926 --> 00:02:00,304
Huh?

43
00:02:01,286 --> 00:02:03,014
So that...

44
00:02:04,606 --> 00:02:05,631
yesterday?

45
00:02:09,015 --> 00:02:12,030
Sigh...
I can never go back to the emergency staircase.

46
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:14,954
Well I think it's a good opportunity.
Why don't you just go along with the flow?

47
00:02:14,954 --> 00:02:16,397
Don't you think so?

48
00:02:16,397 --> 00:02:17,008
Eh??

49
00:02:17,008 --> 00:02:18,371
Even if that happened,

50
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:20,585
but I really liked you,

51
00:02:20,585 --> 00:02:23,193
the only person in my heart would still be you.

52
00:02:23,193 --> 00:02:25,357
What are you saying?

53
00:02:25,357 --> 00:02:26,725
Firstly,

54
00:02:26,725 --> 00:02:29,453
he already has Shizuka-san.

55
00:02:30,157 --> 00:02:33,377
You can't just give up like this,
and not tell him what your heart says.

56
00:02:33,377 --> 00:02:36,470
Why don't you tell him your true feelings for him.

57
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:38,190
Maybe there's still a chance...

58
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:40,417
You might be right there...

59
00:02:47,711 --> 00:02:51,609
I had this feeling that we could be together.

60
00:02:52,872 --> 00:02:54,661
You're very pretty.

61
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:58,737
Pretty...

62
00:03:00,576 --> 00:03:02,573
He said I was very pretty.

63
00:03:02,573 --> 00:03:03,733
Eh?

64
00:03:04,937 --> 00:03:06,692
Well... Hanazawa Rui

65
00:03:06,692 --> 00:03:08,769
saw my new clothes

66
00:03:08,769 --> 00:03:12,326
and said I was very pretty.

67
00:03:12,326 --> 00:03:13,790
You're not kidding?

68
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,549
Tsukushi's Prince Charming?

69
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:19,262
Hanazawa Rui really said that?

70
00:03:20,488 --> 00:03:22,731
I can't just forget about what
happened with Rui.

71
00:03:23,668 --> 00:03:25,748
Don't be like this.
Just forgive him this time.

72
00:03:25,748 --> 00:03:27,825
If he apologises to me,
then I'll forgive him.

73
00:03:27,825 --> 00:03:31,079
Well, it's clear that we all feel lonely
when Rui isn't around.

74
00:03:31,079 --> 00:03:32,476
Nonsense!

75
00:03:32,476 --> 00:03:33,976
It doesn't make a difference
if Rui was here or not.

76
00:03:33,976 --> 00:03:36,425
Don't be so direct when you want to say something

77
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:39,346
Quickly make up with Tsukasa.

78
00:03:39,346 --> 00:03:41,565
Lately,
he's been very touchy.

79
00:03:41,565 --> 00:03:43,079
Perhaps he really is like that.

80
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:45,111
But what made me mad

81
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:48,965
were the rude things he said to you.

82
00:03:51,108 --> 00:03:52,194
But...

83
00:03:52,522 --> 00:03:55,105
You weren't very happy either

84
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,922
when Tsukasa and Tsukushi kissed.

85
00:03:57,922 --> 00:03:58,544
Eh?

86
00:03:59,373 --> 00:04:02,124
You like her a bit.

87
00:04:02,124 --> 00:04:03,651
I know that.

88
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:06,526
See you.

89
00:04:10,253 --> 00:04:14,501
This is like a fight where
both sides are unwilling to give in.

90
00:04:14,501 --> 00:04:17,624
You guys are really stubborn.

91
00:04:18,790 --> 00:04:21,841
Even I cannot compare.

92
00:04:23,125 --> 00:04:24,258
Eh?

93
00:04:24,258 --> 00:04:25,916
Isn't that Makino Tsukushi?

94
00:04:26,309 --> 00:04:27,779
What?

95
00:04:27,779 --> 00:04:29,128
We must stop here, Tsukasa.
Now's the chance...

96
00:04:29,128 --> 00:04:30,032
Eh?

97
00:04:31,548 --> 00:04:34,199
Stop playing a fool.
Don't stop the car.

98
00:04:34,199 --> 00:04:36,208
Checkmate!

99
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,956
Yes!

100
00:04:52,516 --> 00:04:56,122
You must treat her well.

101
00:04:57,253 --> 00:05:02,144
Then I won't have any worries
about taking care of her.

102
00:05:06,212 --> 00:05:07,820
How troublesome...

103
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:08,912
Eh?

104
00:05:08,912 --> 00:05:11,476
You already know my true feelings

105
00:05:11,476 --> 00:05:14,199
Yet you insist that I go for someone else.

106
00:05:16,596 --> 00:05:17,892
Rui...

107
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:21,479
You get it, right?

108
00:05:24,118 --> 00:05:27,006
What are you saying, "having no worries
about taking care of her".

109
00:05:29,475 --> 00:05:31,142
I really don't get it.

110
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:34,121
Rui!

111
00:05:41,949 --> 00:05:43,925
Oh dear.

112
00:05:43,925 --> 00:05:46,958
Rui,
Wait a minute.

113
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,559
Rui!

114
00:05:52,941 --> 00:05:54,135
I...

115
00:05:54,135 --> 00:05:56,170
That's why I came back from France.

116
00:05:58,518 --> 00:06:04,477
It's because I wanted to live
by my own means.

117
00:06:05,882 --> 00:06:07,909
So I decided to come back from France.

118
00:06:10,321 --> 00:06:14,613
To realise my dream of becoming
an international lawyer.

119
00:06:15,092 --> 00:06:17,021
To live up to the name of Toudou.

120
00:06:18,873 --> 00:06:23,967
I don't want to rely on the wealth
that I can inherit from the Toudou family.

121
00:06:25,194 --> 00:06:27,574
But to live in France

122
00:06:28,468 --> 00:06:30,746
as an ordinary person.

