308
00:19:19,544 --> 00:19:20,679
Sis.

309
00:19:20,679 --> 00:19:22,191
Hey look at this.

310
00:19:22,191 --> 00:19:24,239
It's Shizuka-chan.

311
00:19:24,239 --> 00:19:25,230
Oh.

312
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,907
Eh? Shizuka-chan...

313
00:19:27,907 --> 00:19:30,508
When did she start studying overseas?

314
00:19:45,404 --> 00:19:48,281
Tomorrow,

315
00:19:48,281 --> 00:19:50,422
I definitely want to see him.

316
00:20:11,913 --> 00:20:13,112
Yes.

317
00:20:30,393 --> 00:20:32,325
Why isn't he here?

318
00:20:34,318 --> 00:20:37,050
I really want to meet him again!

319
00:20:40,570 --> 00:20:41,757
It can't be...

320
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,354
Eh...

321
00:20:46,354 --> 00:20:47,979
Who do you want to meet again?

322
00:20:47,979 --> 00:20:49,244
Eh?

323
00:20:50,024 --> 00:20:51,739
Umm.. Umm...

324
00:20:54,211 --> 00:20:55,680
Oh yeah... Umm...

325
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:59,093
It's been a while.

326
00:21:02,051 --> 00:21:03,903
Well... This...

327
00:21:03,903 --> 00:21:05,514
Shizuka-san.

328
00:21:06,437 --> 00:21:09,471
She's busy with a lot of things
before she returns to France.

329
00:21:11,884 --> 00:21:13,433
She really...

330
00:21:13,433 --> 00:21:15,624
wants to go back to France.

331
00:21:24,790 --> 00:21:27,979
Are you alright with that?

332
00:21:30,181 --> 00:21:32,025
Well I think...

333
00:21:33,150 --> 00:21:35,241
She's the type that doesn't really care
about what others think.

334
00:21:35,241 --> 00:21:37,955
If she wants to do something,
nothing can stop her.

335
00:22:06,035 --> 00:22:07,518
But then,

336
00:22:08,798 --> 00:22:10,417
if you don't do something...

337
00:22:11,832 --> 00:22:16,176
we won't be able to see her again.

338
00:22:19,484 --> 00:22:21,094
Want to see her?

339
00:22:21,667 --> 00:22:22,464
Eh?

340
00:22:22,464 --> 00:22:26,406
Do you want to see Shizuka again?

341
00:22:27,534 --> 00:22:28,340
Well, no...

342
00:22:28,340 --> 00:22:31,206
Just now you mentioned...

343
00:22:31,206 --> 00:22:33,446
seeing Shizuka again?

344
00:22:33,446 --> 00:22:35,423
Ah...

345
00:22:36,252 --> 00:22:37,195
That's right.

346
00:22:37,195 --> 00:22:42,184
You've said that you really admire Shizuka.

347
00:22:49,082 --> 00:22:51,531
**Toudou**

348
00:22:53,236 --> 00:22:54,191
Miss.

349
00:22:54,191 --> 00:22:56,298
Hanazawa Rui is here to see you.

350
00:22:57,073 --> 00:22:58,364
Ah!

351
00:22:58,364 --> 00:22:59,324
Good evening.

352
00:22:59,324 --> 00:23:00,609
Good evening.

353
00:23:00,609 --> 00:23:03,173
She wants to thank you
about what happeend at the party.

354
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:05,123
There's no need for that.

355
00:23:05,123 --> 00:23:08,236
Your mom?
She still angry?

356
00:23:08,765 --> 00:23:11,046
She agreed for the time being.

357
00:23:11,046 --> 00:23:13,423
But she's still reluctant to completely let go.

358
00:23:13,423 --> 00:23:14,465
I see...

359
00:23:14,465 --> 00:23:16,610
I'll go say "Hi" to your mom.

360
00:23:18,151 --> 00:23:20,884
It's a bit messy,
but come in.

361
00:23:28,958 --> 00:23:31,461
You're... Already preparing to leave.

362
00:23:31,461 --> 00:23:33,104
Although there's still a week left,

363
00:23:33,104 --> 00:23:35,581
it's better to prepare in advance.

364
00:23:35,581 --> 00:23:39,228
A week left...?

365
00:23:39,228 --> 00:23:44,485
Today, I went to school to request
for my withdrawal.

366
00:23:44,485 --> 00:23:47,841
Then... You won't be coming back?

367
00:23:47,841 --> 00:23:49,867
Yea.

368
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:51,498
That's what I've decided.

369
00:24:01,009 --> 00:24:02,159
Can you tell?

370
00:24:02,565 --> 00:24:05,145
That's F4 and I.

371
00:24:05,145 --> 00:24:08,253
The one on the left,
that's Rui and I when we were young.

372
00:24:08,253 --> 00:24:09,897
Isn't it cute?

373
00:24:11,343 --> 00:24:15,070
That kind of smile,
I've never seen it before.

374
00:24:22,529 --> 00:24:24,444
He really...

375
00:24:26,256 --> 00:24:28,884
really liked her...

376
00:24:29,527 --> 00:24:30,955
right from the start.

377
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:39,435
Please don't go back to France.

378
00:24:42,207 --> 00:24:43,747
What are you saying?

379
00:24:43,747 --> 00:24:45,777
For Hanazawa Rui,

380
00:24:45,777 --> 00:24:47,751
I want you to stay in Japan.

381
00:24:48,398 --> 00:24:53,113
He's always around the emergency staircase,

382
00:24:54,204 --> 00:24:57,817
always hoping that Shizuka-san would return.

383
00:24:57,817 --> 00:24:59,883
Everytime he talks about Shizuka-san,

384
00:24:59,883 --> 00:25:03,810
his face will be lit with a warm smile.

385
00:25:03,810 --> 00:25:05,369
But...

386
00:25:05,369 --> 00:25:07,931
Once Shizuka-san decided to leave for France,

387
00:25:07,931 --> 00:25:10,947
he's stopped going there.

388
00:25:11,925 --> 00:25:13,612
He's dissappeared for a while.

389
00:25:13,612 --> 00:25:16,856
And then comes back with such a sad face.

390
00:25:19,330 --> 00:25:23,456
If Shizuka-san returns to France,

391
00:25:23,456 --> 00:25:25,546
Hanazawa Rui will...

392
00:25:25,546 --> 00:25:28,760
not be his true self.

393
00:25:30,727 --> 00:25:33,161
That is why,

394
00:25:33,161 --> 00:25:36,132
I'm asking that you stay in Japan.

395
00:25:38,519 --> 00:25:40,445
I'm sorry,

396
00:25:40,445 --> 00:25:42,881
I cannot do that.

397
00:25:49,301 --> 00:25:51,699
I'm begging you Shizuka-san.

398
00:25:51,699 --> 00:25:53,330
I know that by doing this, it is hard for you.

399
00:25:53,330 --> 00:25:55,199
I know that what I'm doing is very foolish.

400
00:25:55,199 --> 00:25:56,756
Look up at me.

401
00:26:02,345 --> 00:26:04,039
Well for me,

402
00:26:04,039 --> 00:26:06,189
the decisions I make

403
00:26:06,189 --> 00:26:10,456
are just like when buying something overseas.

404
00:26:10,456 --> 00:26:15,135
If I let the chance go and not buy it back,

405
00:26:15,135 --> 00:26:17,827
I won't be able to buy it again.

406
00:26:20,090 --> 00:26:22,991
People will then think

407
00:26:22,991 --> 00:26:27,602
that it's a good chance to buy it,
and continue to live on.

408
00:26:28,928 --> 00:26:30,145
But then,

409
00:26:30,145 --> 00:26:31,719
I...

410
00:26:31,719 --> 00:26:34,903
don't want to be one of those people,

411
00:26:35,879 --> 00:26:40,091
even though I might have regrets later on.

412
00:26:41,079 --> 00:26:48,115
I want to be myself,
living as I choose to live.

413
00:26:52,863 --> 00:26:54,263
I hope you understand.

414
00:27:01,650 --> 00:27:03,258
I understand.

415
00:27:08,795 --> 00:27:11,037
I've said things I shouldn't have, sorry.

416
00:27:11,037 --> 00:27:12,334
No not that.

417
00:27:12,334 --> 00:27:15,939
I'm happy, really.

418
00:27:20,898 --> 00:27:23,683
About Rui,

419
00:27:23,683 --> 00:27:25,055
please take care of him.

420
00:27:29,879 --> 00:27:32,764
I'm really sorry.

421
00:27:38,153 --> 00:27:39,463
What are you doing?

422
00:27:42,879 --> 00:27:43,760
Eh?

423
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:45,784
What was that all about just now?

424
00:27:52,071 --> 00:27:54,827
Who asked you to do that?

425
00:27:57,468 --> 00:28:00,385
I didn't bring you here to do that kind of thing.

426
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:05,231
Was it for me?

427
00:28:06,887 --> 00:28:08,642
What difference does it make?

428
00:28:09,758 --> 00:28:11,626
Mind your own business.

429
00:28:12,506 --> 00:28:14,086
"Mind you own business"?

430
00:28:14,086 --> 00:28:16,127
What are you thinking?

431
00:28:17,298 --> 00:28:19,281
Begging in a place like that.

432
00:28:19,281 --> 00:28:19,949
I...

433
00:28:19,949 --> 00:28:22,891
Why are you doing that?

434
00:28:26,566 --> 00:28:28,564
I really can't believe it.

435
00:28:31,552 --> 00:28:35,675
You look so sad and pitiful.

436
00:28:35,675 --> 00:28:37,592
You won't be able to see her again.

437
00:28:37,592 --> 00:28:39,936
This is none of your business.

438
00:28:44,308 --> 00:28:45,689
Go back.

439
00:28:51,344 --> 00:28:52,554
Go back!

440
00:30:46,766 --> 00:30:48,086
Shizuka.

441
00:30:50,393 --> 00:30:52,438
About what happened at the party...

442
00:30:54,583 --> 00:30:56,494
I understand.

443
00:30:58,162 --> 00:31:01,144
We give you our best wishes.

444
00:31:01,144 --> 00:31:03,829
I give you guys my best wishes as well.

445
00:31:05,627 --> 00:31:07,486
Help me say goodbye to Rui.

446
00:31:14,894 --> 00:31:15,832
See you.

447
00:31:16,301 --> 00:31:17,556
See you.

448
00:31:18,666 --> 00:31:20,586
Well, I'll be off.

449
00:31:20,586 --> 00:31:23,142
Good luck. Have a safe trip.

450
00:31:23,142 --> 00:31:25,293
Thank you.

451
00:31:25,293 --> 00:31:26,236
Good bye.

452
00:31:26,779 --> 00:31:28,709
Shizuka-san!

453
00:31:32,498 --> 00:31:33,868
You came.

454
00:31:35,006 --> 00:31:37,900
I'm very sorry I'm late.

455
00:31:41,253 --> 00:31:42,778
Hanazawa Rui?

456
00:31:42,778 --> 00:31:44,301
He didn't come.

457
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,734
He really is a small kid.

458
00:31:48,088 --> 00:31:49,373
Oh yes.

459
00:31:52,623 --> 00:31:55,062
Here, these are for you?

460
00:31:55,458 --> 00:31:58,111
This pair really looks good on you.

461
00:31:58,111 --> 00:31:59,483
But...

462
00:32:00,451 --> 00:32:04,789
You must let them bring you to wonderful places.

463
00:32:08,802 --> 00:32:10,668
I'll be working hard too.

464
00:32:13,159 --> 00:32:14,176
See you.

465
00:32:16,816 --> 00:32:19,330
See you!

466
00:32:19,330 --> 00:32:20,780
Goodbye everyone.

467
00:32:20,780 --> 00:32:22,782
Good luck!

468
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:34,451
Rui!

469
00:32:37,767 --> 00:32:38,903
What have you been doing?

470
00:32:38,903 --> 00:32:40,358
When did you arrive?

471
00:32:40,358 --> 00:32:41,871
An hour ago.

472
00:32:41,871 --> 00:32:43,393
Then why didn't you come here?

473
00:32:43,393 --> 00:32:45,974
I've been watching you guys.

474
00:32:45,974 --> 00:32:47,726
What an idiot.

475
00:32:50,313 --> 00:32:51,865
Go after her!

476
00:32:53,174 --> 00:32:54,732
If you like her,

477
00:32:54,732 --> 00:32:57,654
you have to go after her, right?

478
00:32:57,654 --> 00:33:00,264
Are you just going to be satisfied watching?

479
00:33:00,264 --> 00:33:03,020
Do you still consider yourself a man?

480
00:33:03,020 --> 00:33:05,224
I'll go.

481
00:33:05,224 --> 00:33:06,419
Eh?

482
00:33:07,016 --> 00:33:09,968
I'll be leaving for France

483
00:33:09,968 --> 00:33:11,296
as well.

484
00:33:12,279 --> 00:33:13,272
Rui

485
00:33:13,272 --> 00:33:14,459
You kidding.

486
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:15,693
Makino.

487
00:33:17,131 --> 00:33:19,451
Well I...

488
00:33:19,451 --> 00:33:22,416
really like your determination.

489
00:33:23,305 --> 00:33:25,719
That's what I really lack.

490
00:33:27,578 --> 00:33:29,567
I finally realised that

491
00:33:30,369 --> 00:33:32,895
I can't continue like this.

492
00:33:35,005 --> 00:33:36,277
Thank you.

493
00:33:58,603 --> 00:34:00,117
Wait a minute, Rui!

494
00:34:06,150 --> 00:34:07,819
Are you really leaving?

495
00:34:10,322 --> 00:34:11,169
Yes.

496
00:34:14,655 --> 00:34:16,595
Why??

497
00:34:16,595 --> 00:34:19,513
Why didn't you come to us to talk about it?

498
00:34:21,445 --> 00:34:22,552
I'm sorry...

499
00:34:27,696 --> 00:34:31,666
Haven't we been together all this while?

500
00:34:31,666 --> 00:34:34,027
Why do you suddenly want to leave us?

501
00:34:37,098 --> 00:34:39,251
Why??

502
00:34:39,251 --> 00:34:41,479
Where did you suddenly get the idea from?

503
00:34:42,810 --> 00:34:44,443
Tsukasa. About last time...

504
00:34:44,443 --> 00:34:46,560
It doesn't matter any more.

505
00:34:48,598 --> 00:34:50,162
Say,

506
00:34:52,529 --> 00:34:54,405
do you really want to go?

507
00:34:57,872 --> 00:34:59,769
Rui

508
00:35:03,490 --> 00:35:05,057
Stop playing with us.

509
00:35:05,729 --> 00:35:10,001
If you really are leaving,
we won't have you around anymore.

510
00:35:11,942 --> 00:35:14,058
Does it really not matter to you?

511
00:35:16,346 --> 00:35:17,981
Rui!

512
00:35:20,401 --> 00:35:22,161
Take care,

513
00:35:22,161 --> 00:35:23,194
Tsukasa.

514
00:35:28,826 --> 00:35:30,768
In Paris...

515
00:35:30,768 --> 00:35:33,116
If you meet any bad people in Paris

516
00:35:33,116 --> 00:35:35,220
tell me immediately.

517
00:35:35,220 --> 00:35:37,711
The three of us will fly there to help.

518
00:35:39,167 --> 00:35:41,450
Ya...

519
00:35:41,450 --> 00:35:42,847
You got it?

520
00:35:44,506 --> 00:35:47,609
Thank you. I'll be off.

521
00:35:58,962 --> 00:36:00,279
Tsukasa.

522
00:36:02,654 --> 00:36:03,593
Take it.

523
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:10,320
Rui!

524
00:36:36,639 --> 00:36:38,229
Bye bye...

525
00:36:38,229 --> 00:36:39,370
Hanazawa Rui.

526
00:36:40,941 --> 00:36:42,265
Rui!!

527
00:36:43,157 --> 00:36:44,571
Good luck!

528
00:36:45,121 --> 00:36:49,234
Rui! Take care!

529
00:36:50,272 --> 00:36:51,857
Rui!

530
00:36:55,897 --> 00:36:57,181
Rui!

531
00:36:57,181 --> 00:37:00,705
My opinion of him has changed a little.

532
00:37:02,414 --> 00:37:05,108
That's the bond between men.

533
00:37:05,581 --> 00:37:09,014
Well that guy is full of surprises.

534
00:37:09,014 --> 00:37:10,482
Old lady...

535
00:37:10,482 --> 00:37:13,612
Of all the men I've met before,

536
00:37:13,612 --> 00:37:17,124
some put on a "tiger mask".

537
00:37:17,124 --> 00:37:18,379
It has begun...

538
00:37:18,379 --> 00:37:21,649
They appear very frightening, and violent.

539
00:37:21,649 --> 00:37:24,948
But those men are actually soft-hearted.

540
00:37:25,299 --> 00:37:26,926
He's actually sending whatever money they can spare

541
00:37:26,926 --> 00:37:30,185
back home to help out in the finances.

542
00:37:30,185 --> 00:37:32,116
Didn't you say they have "tiger masks"?

543
00:37:32,116 --> 00:37:33,699
Well he...

544
00:37:33,699 --> 00:37:36,287
cannot allow his true lonely self

545
00:37:36,287 --> 00:37:38,702
to be seen by others.

546
00:37:38,702 --> 00:37:41,954
At that time,
the only person who could understand him well

547
00:37:41,954 --> 00:37:44,264
would be me alone.

548
00:37:46,116 --> 00:37:49,493
I really have no idea what she's talking about.

549
00:37:51,053 --> 00:37:53,793
I never got to it after all.

550
00:38:02,386 --> 00:38:04,548
To Rui

551
00:38:05,795 --> 00:38:09,968
How's Paris?

552
00:38:09,968 --> 00:38:12,379
How are you?

553
00:38:23,242 --> 00:38:28,230
Do you...

554
00:38:28,230 --> 00:38:32,361
like...

555
00:38:32,361 --> 00:38:33,560
Makino Tsukushi?

556
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:35,579
What are you writing?

557
00:38:35,579 --> 00:38:37,469
Maybe you're writing a love letter!

558
00:38:37,469 --> 00:38:38,473
Of course not!

559
00:38:38,473 --> 00:38:41,469
Didn't I say not to come in as you like?
Hey wait...

560
00:38:42,376 --> 00:38:46,181
"Kazu"??
(He wrote "Kazu" instead of "Rui", they look alike)

561
00:38:46,181 --> 00:38:48,306
It's "Rui", idiot.

562
00:38:48,927 --> 00:38:51,116
Don't tell me you can't even recognise simple Kanji.

563
00:38:52,147 --> 00:38:54,135
I think it's better if I write it for you.

564
00:38:54,135 --> 00:38:57,743
Why?
How do I convey my personal feelings to him if you write it?

565
00:38:58,206 --> 00:39:02,302
Tsukasa,
what do you have left to say to him?

566
00:39:02,302 --> 00:39:03,320
That guy...

567
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:06,263
going to France to go after Shizuka.

568
00:39:06,263 --> 00:39:09,305
Oh... So that's how it was.

569
00:39:09,305 --> 00:39:10,905
He's done well, that Rui.

570
00:39:10,905 --> 00:39:12,384
Are you kidding?

571
00:39:13,204 --> 00:39:15,675
He even left his best friends behind.

572
00:39:15,675 --> 00:39:20,432
When you love, you wish to do things for it.

573
00:39:20,432 --> 00:39:23,187
You wish to sacrifice for it.

574
00:39:23,187 --> 00:39:25,545
You wish to serve for it.

575
00:39:25,545 --> 00:39:26,358
Huh?

576
00:39:26,358 --> 00:39:29,004
That's from Hemingway's short story.
(pg 72, A Farewell to Arms by Ernest Hemingway)

577
00:39:30,102 --> 00:39:33,340
When you truly love someone,

578
00:39:33,340 --> 00:39:35,275
you will understand what I said.

579
00:39:37,707 --> 00:39:39,554
But until then, Tsukasa,

580
00:39:39,554 --> 00:39:41,191
you must treasure the person

581
00:39:41,191 --> 00:39:43,022
whom you really like.

582
00:39:43,022 --> 00:39:44,309
You must remember,

583
00:39:44,309 --> 00:39:47,811
you musn't be too fast in relationships. And...
(Tsukasa interprets what his sister says wrongly,
you'll see later)

584
00:39:47,811 --> 00:39:50,906
you can't just buy a person's heart with money.

585
00:39:50,906 --> 00:39:53,593
In order to be loved,

586
00:39:53,593 --> 00:39:57,032
you must first give your love.

587
00:39:59,773 --> 00:40:01,945
My goodness, sis.

588
00:40:01,945 --> 00:40:03,653
I now...

589
00:40:03,653 --> 00:40:05,555
feel like lightning has struck me.
(Tsukasa's Japanese fails)

590
00:40:05,555 --> 00:40:07,903
What "lightning has struck me"?
Your choice of words is wrong again.

591
00:40:07,903 --> 00:40:09,783
I need to completely change my perception.

592
00:40:09,783 --> 00:40:11,489
How can perception be changed...

593
00:40:11,489 --> 00:40:12,748
You really are great, sis.

594
00:40:12,748 --> 00:40:14,283
Thanks a lot!

595
00:40:14,283 --> 00:40:16,776
When you leave the country tomorrow,
be sure to come back safely.

596
00:40:16,776 --> 00:40:19,332
What a wonderful suggestion.

597
00:40:19,332 --> 00:40:21,101
The next time you come back

598
00:40:21,101 --> 00:40:23,777
I'll definitely have something for you to see.

599
00:40:28,671 --> 00:40:30,964
Is it okay, just leaving like this?

600
00:40:30,964 --> 00:40:32,753
OK! OK!

601
00:40:42,683 --> 00:40:45,047
Thank you for the food.

602
00:40:45,047 --> 00:40:48,746
Such a pity that Rui-san is gone.

603
00:40:48,746 --> 00:40:51,361
Shizuka-san won't be returning too.

604
00:40:51,361 --> 00:40:53,742
Tsubaki-san is also leaving soon.

605
00:40:53,742 --> 00:40:59,071
It seems like those who have been defending you
have all gone.

606
00:41:04,669 --> 00:41:06,832
If you want to fight, go ahead.

607
00:41:06,832 --> 00:41:09,243
Since when have I depended on anyone else?

608
00:41:09,243 --> 00:41:10,723
Don't be so quick to say...

609
00:41:12,493 --> 00:41:14,856
Ah... I've been accidentally pushed over
by Doumyoji-sama...

610
00:41:14,856 --> 00:41:16,691
Shut up,
you ugly witch.

611
00:41:16,691 --> 00:41:18,257
How cruel.

612
00:41:18,257 --> 00:41:19,921
Yuriko...

613
00:41:22,337 --> 00:41:23,520
What?

614
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:24,862
Woah...

615
00:41:25,879 --> 00:41:30,704
Oh my... I must go one round.
(The Japanese words actually translate to
"I musn't be too fast")

616
00:41:31,601 --> 00:41:32,500
Eh?

617
00:41:35,417 --> 00:41:39,957
Sunday, 1pm at the open area
at "Ebisu Garden Place" near the clock.

618
00:41:44,931 --> 00:41:49,114
Why? Why is the wealthy Doumyoji-sama
going out with a girl like her?

619
00:41:49,114 --> 00:41:51,279
Even I have not heard of such a thing happening...

620
00:41:51,279 --> 00:41:54,848
Which means, he wants to date her...

621
00:42:11,506 --> 00:42:12,895
Umm...

622
00:42:13,449 --> 00:42:14,917
Huh?

623
00:42:18,955 --> 00:42:20,157
What is it?!

624
00:42:20,157 --> 00:42:24,122
About just now...

625
00:42:24,879 --> 00:42:26,404
What about it?

626
00:42:26,404 --> 00:42:28,805
I don't know nothing, stupid.

627
00:42:30,322 --> 00:42:33,345
Anyway,

628
00:42:33,345 --> 00:42:35,500
Hemingway

629
00:42:35,500 --> 00:42:37,935
Heming...?

630
00:42:38,946 --> 00:42:40,794
You should really read more.

631
00:43:05,751 --> 00:43:07,482
I think I'm a little early.

632
00:43:09,377 --> 00:43:13,697
Well then, if she doesn't come 5 minutes before 1pm,
I'll show her...

633
00:43:14,642 --> 00:43:16,845
Isn't it today? Are you sure it's okay to not go?

634
00:43:17,260 --> 00:43:21,741
Why must I pitifully spend my Sunday
with a guy like him?

635
00:43:21,741 --> 00:43:24,286
If you don't go, he might seriously take revenge.

636
00:43:24,978 --> 00:43:26,366
That's true...

637
00:43:26,908 --> 00:43:30,360
If you go, it's hell. If you don't go, it's still hell.

638
00:43:31,539 --> 00:43:35,889
Well I'm already in a fight with him,
he can wait all he wants.

639
00:43:36,505 --> 00:43:38,875
Ah... That's pretty!

640
00:43:49,590 --> 00:43:51,441
Sorry.

641
00:43:51,441 --> 00:43:53,293
I'm late.

642
00:43:58,188 --> 00:43:59,752
I'm going to beat her up.

643
00:44:01,186 --> 00:44:03,497
Thanks for the food!

644
00:44:04,424 --> 00:44:06,289
Wait a minute...

645
00:44:08,188 --> 00:44:09,125
How's it?

646
00:44:09,750 --> 00:44:10,667
How's it?

647
00:44:11,307 --> 00:44:13,270
How 'bout that...

648
00:44:13,270 --> 00:44:14,918
Oh, so pretty!

649
00:44:36,551 --> 00:44:37,935
What kind of toy is that?

650
00:44:37,935 --> 00:44:40,458
I think it should be "tiger mask".

651
00:44:43,569 --> 00:44:45,142
Oh, how cute.

652
00:44:45,837 --> 00:44:47,555
Oh yea, that old lady mentioned before...

653
00:44:47,542 --> 00:44:50,723
Men with a "tiger mask" aren't able to show

654
00:44:50,723 --> 00:44:53,089
their true, lonely, self to other people.

655
00:45:04,885 --> 00:45:06,625
Rui!

656
00:45:16,285 --> 00:45:17,689
I'm sorry, Yuuki.

657
00:45:18,331 --> 00:45:19,972
Wait a minute! Tsukushi!

658
00:45:21,421 --> 00:45:22,686
Where are you going?

659
00:45:29,318 --> 00:45:30,778
Hemingway

660
00:45:33,681 --> 00:45:37,563
Sunday, 1pm at the open area
at "Ebisu Garden Place" near the clock.

661
00:45:38,161 --> 00:45:40,340
He wants to date me?

662
00:45:40,966 --> 00:45:42,553
It can't be true.

663
00:45:43,463 --> 00:45:45,765
It can never happen.

664
00:45:46,636 --> 00:45:48,765
It's already so late,

665
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:51,771
he'll definitely not be there.

666
00:45:53,014 --> 00:45:54,544
He won't be...

667
00:46:08,920 --> 00:46:10,599
Unbelievable...

668
00:46:13,236 --> 00:46:14,510
Why?

669
00:46:20,424 --> 00:46:21,920
This is the girl I like.

670
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:24,093
Go check on what Tsukasa is doing.

671
00:46:24,093 --> 00:46:26,405
You're pretty, let's go.

672
00:46:28,860 --> 00:46:31,060
What's this about?

673
00:46:32,826 --> 00:46:35,198
You must be serious about this, Tsukushi.

674
00:46:35,643 --> 00:46:37,256
What are you doing?

675
00:46:47,823 --> 00:46:48,973
I believed you...

